<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,303,919,945]" box="[189,303,919,945]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,919,945]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,919,945]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1398,968,1071]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
The new species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[558,710,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenescens">
<emphasis box="[558,710,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. aenescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Collin J. E." box="[866,1005,968,994]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="385 - 420" refId="ref6393" refString="Collin J. E. 1960. Some Empididae from Palestine. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 2: 385 - 420. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222935908650872" type="journal article" year="1960">Collin 1960</bibRefCitation>
as referred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith K. G. V." box="[1178,1336,968,995]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref6677" refString="Smith K. G. V. 1967. Afrikanische Empididae (Dipt.). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A 179: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1967">Smith (1967)</bibRefCitation>
. This group is characterized by the right surstylus, which is split up in two or more lobes. The dorsal lobe has a broad tip with a small apical point (
<figureCitation box="[626,718,1044,1070]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[206,1371,1394,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[189,1399,1361,1883]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 8. Crossopalpus complicatus sp. nov., male holotype, terminalia (leg. P. Grootaert and I. Van de Velde, RBINS). A. Right surstyli. B. Lateral view of right epandrial lamella. C. Dorsal view of epandrium, with detail of left surstyli. D. Tip of right surstylus from inside. Scales: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3236111/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) and the ventral lobe is generally set with long bristles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,731,1112,1139]" box="[189,731,1112,1139]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,731,1112,1139]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,731,1112,1139]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Key to male 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1857" box="[346,509,1112,1139]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[346,509,1112,1139]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Crossopalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[585,731,1112,1139]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
