<keyLead box="[189,1399,1162,1189]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
1. Hind tibia with strong dorsal bristles (
<figureCitation box="[680,753,1162,1188]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,897,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[189,1399,897,1923]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Crossopalpus salensis sp. nov., male holotype, habitus (leg. P. Grootaert and I. Van de Velde, RBINS)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3236103/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); antenna entirely black ............................................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1399,1162,1265]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<keyLead pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
– Hind tibiae with weak dorsal bristles (
<figureCitation box="[672,743,1200,1227]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1967,1993]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,1028,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,1028,1924]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Crossopalpus complicatus sp. nov., male holotype, habitus (leg. P. Grootaert and I. Van de Velde, RBINS)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3236109/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), but long ventrals; pedicel contrastingly reddish yellow, scape and postpedicel black ........................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Grootaert &amp; Velde, 2019" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Velde" authorityYear="2019" box="[1122,1301,1238,1265]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="complicatus" status="sp. nov.">
